1
00:00:20,458 --> 00:00:23,333
[NARRATOR] Akihabara,
the otaku city of dreams,

2
00:00:23,416 --> 00:00:25,916
is now under attack from
mysterious monstrosities

3
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:28,375
known as the Bugged Ones.

4
00:00:28,458 --> 00:00:30,541
Some brave citizens have
formed vigilante groups

5
00:00:30,625 --> 00:00:32,250
to resist this Buggy scourge,

6
00:00:32,333 --> 00:00:35,625
but the invasion intensifies
with each new day.

7
00:00:35,708 --> 00:00:38,125
This is the story
of Tamotsu Denkigai,

8
00:00:38,208 --> 00:00:40,458
a young man given
Bugged Ones powers,

9
00:00:40,541 --> 00:00:42,833
turned from superfan
into superhero.

10
00:00:42,916 --> 00:00:45,541
Can he and his merry band
save the greatest shopping

11
00:00:45,625 --> 00:00:47,541
neighborhood in the world?!

12
00:00:55,916 --> 00:00:58,208
Come on. It's cool my
parents sent me food,

13
00:00:58,291 --> 00:01:00,500
but can't they get
with the decade?

14
00:01:00,583 --> 00:01:03,000
[NIWAKA]
Look, bro! Mom sent you rice!

15
00:01:03,083 --> 00:01:05,208
Wow! That looks like
some high-quality stuff!

16
00:01:05,291 --> 00:01:07,625
When do we eat?

17
00:01:07,708 --> 00:01:09,333
But then I guess if
the base actually had

18
00:01:09,416 --> 00:01:11,250
a rice cooker,
it wouldn't be a problem.

19
00:01:11,333 --> 00:01:12,541
Yes, as great as our Ma is,

20
00:01:12,625 --> 00:01:14,250
she doesn't seem to
be much of a cook.

21
00:01:14,333 --> 00:01:16,041
Loves to eat, though!

22
00:01:16,125 --> 00:01:17,208
Yeah!

23
00:01:17,291 --> 00:01:19,041
Oh shut up, you guys.
We all have things

24
00:01:19,125 --> 00:01:20,666
we're good at and
eating's one of mine.

25
00:01:20,750 --> 00:01:22,666
Tamotsu doesn't cook either!

26
00:01:22,750 --> 00:01:25,416
Whoa, hey! Just 'cause I don't
cook, doesn't mean I can't!

27
00:01:25,500 --> 00:01:27,666
Oh god, don't get
him started on that.

28
00:01:27,750 --> 00:01:29,333
That seems like the
kind of thing Tamotsu

29
00:01:29,416 --> 00:01:30,916
would spend too much money on!

30
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:33,666
You're not wrong. That reminds
me of the time he got obsessed

31
00:01:33,750 --> 00:01:35,541
with making his own curry.

32
00:01:35,625 --> 00:01:38,166
He spent hours hand-picking
and mixing spices.

33
00:01:38,250 --> 00:01:40,583
Then nursed the soup for
three days without sleep!

34
00:01:40,666 --> 00:01:43,291
He chose his rice
one grain at a time!

35
00:01:43,375 --> 00:01:45,791
It took him a whole week just
to finish cooking one meal!

36
00:01:45,875 --> 00:01:47,666
You didn't even mention
my craft pickling!

37
00:01:47,750 --> 00:01:48,958
[ARISA]
Oh, don't worry.

38
00:01:49,041 --> 00:01:51,166
Next time you want
some curry, you can ask me!

39
00:01:51,250 --> 00:01:52,791
Wait, really?
You can do that too?

40
00:01:52,875 --> 00:01:54,291
You bet, I'm a curry master!

41
00:01:54,375 --> 00:01:55,750
Wow.

42
00:01:55,833 --> 00:01:56,416
Uh...

43
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:57,833
Huh?

44
00:01:59,166 --> 00:02:01,166
[TAMOTSU] What's going on?
Some kind of street show?

45
00:02:01,250 --> 00:02:03,583
Look! What are those things?

46
00:02:03,666 --> 00:02:04,750
[ALL]
Huh?

47
00:02:04,833 --> 00:02:06,875
I think they're boxes.

48
00:02:10,833 --> 00:02:13,250
Wow. How is that even possible?

49
00:02:13,333 --> 00:02:14,625
Yeah, they look heavy.

50
00:02:14,708 --> 00:02:16,375
Why is his neck not snapping?

51
00:02:16,458 --> 00:02:17,333
[ARISA]
I know him!

52
00:02:17,416 --> 00:02:18,625
[TAMOTSU, NIWAKA, MATOME]
Huh?

53
00:02:18,708 --> 00:02:21,875
He... He's my old master!

54
00:02:26,666 --> 00:02:31,625
♪

55
00:03:57,125 --> 00:03:58,916
[TAMOTSU]
You sure about this, Arisa?

56
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:01,166
Yeah. When he passed us
he didn't react at all.

57
00:04:01,250 --> 00:04:02,875
There's no way I could
forget that face,

58
00:04:02,958 --> 00:04:04,791
he was definitely my
old kung-fu master,

59
00:04:04,875 --> 00:04:06,166
from my training days in China!

60
00:04:06,250 --> 00:04:07,625
You trained in China?!

61
00:04:07,708 --> 00:04:09,916
Interesting. Well that explains
how you're so strong.

62
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:13,250
That's right. The training he
put me through was super tough.

63
00:04:13,333 --> 00:04:14,791
But it was such a
rewarding experience,

64
00:04:14,875 --> 00:04:15,833
because up until then,

65
00:04:15,916 --> 00:04:17,958
my life had been
nothing but school.

66
00:04:18,041 --> 00:04:22,250
Ten years ago, I graduated from
Ultimate University in the U.S.

67
00:04:22,333 --> 00:04:24,041
I'd been obsessed
with academics,

68
00:04:24,125 --> 00:04:25,458
so after I got my diploma,

69
00:04:25,541 --> 00:04:27,666
I started traveling to figure
out what to do next.

70
00:04:27,750 --> 00:04:29,666
[TAMOTSU] Hold on, you have
a college degree?!

71
00:04:29,750 --> 00:04:31,666
[MATOME]
So you're actually smart?

72
00:04:31,750 --> 00:04:33,458
[ARISA]
I wanted to find my passion,

73
00:04:33,541 --> 00:04:36,416
something to commit my life to.
I thought travelling around

74
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:38,791
the world would open my eyes
to all the possibilities,

75
00:04:38,875 --> 00:04:41,083
so I could see what
spoke to me most.

76
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:45,791
I perfected
curry-making in India,

77
00:04:45,875 --> 00:04:48,250
explored the finer points of
British humor in England.

78
00:04:48,333 --> 00:04:50,583
And harnessed my wild side
in the African jungle!

79
00:04:50,666 --> 00:04:52,833
That's amazing, Arisa!
You've been everywhere!

80
00:04:52,916 --> 00:04:54,458
Must've been exhausting.

81
00:04:54,541 --> 00:04:57,041
This escalator's not long enough
for the full list, but let's

82
00:04:57,125 --> 00:04:59,458
just say I've tried lots of
things in lots of countries.

83
00:04:59,541 --> 00:05:03,250
And one of them was learning
kung-fu with my master in China.

84
00:05:04,916 --> 00:05:06,208
[ARISA]
I only trained for a year,

85
00:05:06,291 --> 00:05:08,375
but I can't describe
how much it meant to me.

86
00:05:08,458 --> 00:05:11,708
He didn't just train my body,
he trained my heart.

87
00:05:11,791 --> 00:05:15,541
Whether I was facing my fears,
overcoming giant obstacles,

88
00:05:15,625 --> 00:05:18,916
or simply learning to relax,
he was with me all the way.

89
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:21,041
Then finally after I
mastered the martial arts,

90
00:05:21,125 --> 00:05:23,083
it was time to move on,
so I came here to master

91
00:05:23,166 --> 00:05:25,291
the equally-sacred
art of the otaku.

92
00:05:25,375 --> 00:05:28,041
So that's the story of
how you came to Japan, huh?

93
00:05:28,125 --> 00:05:29,500
I just thought you
were a foreigner

94
00:05:29,583 --> 00:05:30,791
who got on the wrong plane.

95
00:05:30,875 --> 00:05:32,291
You silly!

96
00:05:32,375 --> 00:05:34,583
But that doesn't explain why
your old master's in Akiba.

97
00:05:34,666 --> 00:05:36,500
I know, that's a
mystery to me, too.

98
00:05:36,583 --> 00:05:39,125
He did want to take his
family to see Japan one day,

99
00:05:39,208 --> 00:05:41,166
so maybe that's it.

100
00:05:41,250 --> 00:05:44,083
[giggles] Anyway, back to
the rice cooker!

101
00:05:49,541 --> 00:05:51,291
[NIWAKA] Never heard of
a rice cooker shortage.

102
00:05:51,375 --> 00:05:53,166
How can every brand be sold out?

103
00:05:53,250 --> 00:05:55,083
And the display models too?

104
00:05:55,166 --> 00:05:57,083
[CLERK A] Sorry. As you
see we're completely out,

105
00:05:57,166 --> 00:05:59,125
you'll have to wait for
our next shipment.

106
00:05:59,208 --> 00:06:01,208
Sir! But we have
a rice emergency!

107
00:06:01,291 --> 00:06:03,625
Is it normal for rice
cookers to sell out?

108
00:06:03,708 --> 00:06:05,166
Must've been a real
shopping spree.

109
00:06:05,250 --> 00:06:07,250
[gasps]
Look Tamotsu, over there!

110
00:06:07,333 --> 00:06:08,750
Huh?

111
00:06:10,041 --> 00:06:11,333
Walking boxes again?

112
00:06:11,416 --> 00:06:12,791
Could it be?

113
00:06:14,833 --> 00:06:16,291
Actually, he's the
one who bought

114
00:06:16,375 --> 00:06:18,541
all the rice cookers today.
He's my new favorite customer.

115
00:06:18,625 --> 00:06:19,875
Wait up!

116
00:06:19,958 --> 00:06:22,000
Listen, I need a--

117
00:06:22,083 --> 00:06:25,291
[TAMOTSU grunts]
Hey, I'm talking to you, dude!

118
00:06:25,375 --> 00:06:28,541
[ARISA] It's been a
long time, Master!

119
00:06:30,125 --> 00:06:31,958
Moi, you should have told
me you were coming here,

120
00:06:32,041 --> 00:06:34,166
I'd be happy to show you around!

121
00:06:39,125 --> 00:06:42,083
What do we have here? Did you
run into somebody you know?

122
00:06:42,166 --> 00:06:43,291
How bizarre.

123
00:06:43,375 --> 00:06:45,541
I could stare at her
attack powers all day!

124
00:06:45,625 --> 00:06:47,416
[groans]

125
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:50,208
Who in the world are you, lady?
You know my master?

126
00:06:50,291 --> 00:06:52,416
[RISA] I think "knowing him"
is an understatement,

127
00:06:52,500 --> 00:06:54,625
considering how
important I am to him.

128
00:06:54,708 --> 00:06:57,625
The name's Diva Risa McWhite.
I'm his manager.

129
00:06:57,708 --> 00:07:01,125
Diva Risa McWhite, really?
The Diva Risa McWhite?

130
00:07:01,208 --> 00:07:02,708
You know her?

131
00:07:02,791 --> 00:07:05,250
She's a mysterious promoter who
came out of nowhere in the world

132
00:07:05,333 --> 00:07:06,708
of competitive martial arts.

133
00:07:06,791 --> 00:07:09,083
She's been causing gigantic
waves in the industry

134
00:07:09,166 --> 00:07:11,000
and is famous not only
for how well she works

135
00:07:11,083 --> 00:07:12,916
behind the scenes,
but in the spotlight too!

136
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,458
She's ultra-aggressive
with promoting

137
00:07:14,541 --> 00:07:16,875
and sometimes even jumps in
the ring and wins herself!

138
00:07:16,958 --> 00:07:20,083
A promoter, huh? So what's
she doing with your master?

139
00:07:20,166 --> 00:07:23,208
The answer to that
is obvious, you amateur.

140
00:07:23,291 --> 00:07:26,875
I'm using this talented fighter
as my tool to conquer Akiba!

141
00:07:26,958 --> 00:07:28,083
[TAMOTSU]
How's that obvious?

142
00:07:28,166 --> 00:07:29,583
[MATOME] And what's
martial arts promoting

143
00:07:29,666 --> 00:07:31,041
have to do with rice cookers?

144
00:07:31,125 --> 00:07:32,916
[RISA] Nothing, so they
won't see it coming!

145
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:36,125
I'll use his foreign status to
buy goods at duty-free discounts

146
00:07:36,208 --> 00:07:38,791
then resell to Japanese at
full price to warp demand

147
00:07:38,875 --> 00:07:40,333
and confuse the market.

148
00:07:40,416 --> 00:07:42,916
And in that economic chaos,
we will swoop in and conquer!

149
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,083
That's the craziest
plan I've heard yet.

150
00:07:45,166 --> 00:07:48,000
And I thought internet
resellers were bad.

151
00:07:48,083 --> 00:07:50,541
Only a Bugged One
could be that evil!

152
00:07:50,625 --> 00:07:53,750
Guilty as charged. I admit
you've guessed well.

153
00:07:53,833 --> 00:07:55,916
Now you can die!

154
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:56,791
[BOTH gasp]

155
00:07:56,875 --> 00:07:57,916
Cue the usual song and dance!

156
00:07:58,000 --> 00:07:59,750
Not my Master!

157
00:08:03,375 --> 00:08:04,875
Oh, no!

158
00:08:04,958 --> 00:08:07,458
[RISA] Yes, I've turned him into
my slave, buying my rice cookers

159
00:08:07,541 --> 00:08:10,291
and carrying them on his big
strong kung-fu master head.

160
00:08:10,375 --> 00:08:13,333
That's unforgivable!
For the neck strain alone!

161
00:08:13,416 --> 00:08:14,583
It can't be true.

162
00:08:14,666 --> 00:08:16,208
My master wouldn't be
controlled that easily!

163
00:08:16,291 --> 00:08:18,958
Look at his hair, Arisa.
It's not up for debate.

164
00:08:19,041 --> 00:08:22,083
[RISA chuckles] I'm afraid we
can't carry out our plans

165
00:08:22,166 --> 00:08:23,666
with all you flies
buzzing around,

166
00:08:23,750 --> 00:08:25,458
so it's time to bring
out the swatter.

167
00:08:25,541 --> 00:08:28,166
[gasps, groans]

168
00:08:28,250 --> 00:08:29,583
Master!

169
00:08:29,666 --> 00:08:32,125
[RISA chuckles] Unless you're
the masochistic type,

170
00:08:32,208 --> 00:08:34,875
I suggest you leave
while you still can.

171
00:08:39,416 --> 00:08:42,166
Look at him, Tamotsu.
He's strong.

172
00:08:42,250 --> 00:08:43,750
Guys. Stand back.

173
00:08:43,833 --> 00:08:46,333
[ARISA gasps] Master, you can
fight through this!

174
00:08:46,416 --> 00:08:49,625
Your mind's far too
strong to be taken over!

175
00:08:49,708 --> 00:08:50,166
[MASTER shouts]

176
00:08:50,250 --> 00:08:51,166
[ARISA groans]

177
00:08:51,250 --> 00:08:53,083
[TAMOTSU]
Arisa!

178
00:08:53,166 --> 00:08:55,625
I did warn you not
to stick around.

179
00:08:55,708 --> 00:08:57,583
Take care of them, slave!

180
00:08:57,666 --> 00:08:58,958
Here he comes!

181
00:08:59,041 --> 00:09:02,916
[MATOME grunts, shouts]

182
00:09:04,708 --> 00:09:07,125
[TAMOTSU grunts, shouts]

183
00:09:10,791 --> 00:09:11,458
[BOTH grunt]

184
00:09:11,541 --> 00:09:13,666
[NIWAKA]
You okay?

185
00:09:13,750 --> 00:09:14,916
[TAMOTSU, NIWAKA gasp]

186
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:15,833
[ARISA shouts]

187
00:09:15,916 --> 00:09:16,708
[gasps]

188
00:09:16,791 --> 00:09:18,500
This is my battle.

189
00:09:34,458 --> 00:09:37,666
[CLERK A] My dear shoppers.
While the customer is usually

190
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:40,041
always right, we do draw
the line at grappling.

191
00:09:40,125 --> 00:09:42,166
And as you see you're
stopping others from doing

192
00:09:42,250 --> 00:09:44,250
their shopping,
which is a cardinal sin.

193
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:46,875
If you'd like to keep fighting,
I will take appropriate action,

194
00:09:46,958 --> 00:09:49,125
which may include calling
security and the dreaded

195
00:09:49,208 --> 00:09:52,416
nuclear option of revoking
your frequent shopper points.

196
00:09:52,500 --> 00:09:54,458
[ALL]
No! We're sorry!

197
00:09:59,666 --> 00:10:01,083
That sales clerk was
really something.

198
00:10:01,166 --> 00:10:03,666
If saving Akiba meant ruining
people's shopping trips,

199
00:10:03,750 --> 00:10:06,083
then would we really be
saving Akiba at all?

200
00:10:06,166 --> 00:10:07,791
That's a tragic dilemma for you,

201
00:10:07,875 --> 00:10:10,125
but we can't just let
our fight fizzle out.

202
00:10:10,208 --> 00:10:12,583
So why don't you let
me provide the arena?

203
00:10:12,666 --> 00:10:13,875
Say what?

204
00:10:13,958 --> 00:10:16,250
I mean a truly epic
venue that befits a battle

205
00:10:16,333 --> 00:10:18,166
between kung-fu masters.

206
00:10:18,250 --> 00:10:22,083
Yes. Let the Akiba Grand
Tournament begin!

207
00:10:22,166 --> 00:10:23,958
[ALL gasp]

208
00:10:25,125 --> 00:10:27,333
If that's how it has to be.

209
00:10:38,708 --> 00:10:42,500
[FANS cheering]

210
00:10:42,583 --> 00:10:43,958
[MASUTO]
No doubt about it, Kage,

211
00:10:44,041 --> 00:10:46,083
the feeling in this
arena is electric!

212
00:10:46,166 --> 00:10:47,875
[KAGE]
Yeah, this turnout's incredible!

213
00:10:47,958 --> 00:10:49,916
I bet anyone who thought you
couldn't set up a ring in the

214
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:52,333
middle of a shopping district
feels dumb right now!

215
00:10:52,416 --> 00:10:53,791
Well I know I do!

216
00:10:53,875 --> 00:10:55,250
[BOTH gasp]

217
00:10:55,333 --> 00:10:57,125
--[FAN A] Yeah! Bring it on!
--[FAN B] Woo, here we go!

218
00:11:12,291 --> 00:11:13,916
♪

219
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:16,666
[ANNOUNCER]
Ladies and gentlemen!

220
00:11:16,750 --> 00:11:20,750
Introducing the first fighter!
From Hunan China,

221
00:11:20,833 --> 00:11:24,083
weighing in at 154 pounds!

222
00:11:24,166 --> 00:11:30,416
He's the kung-fu champion
of the world, Master!

223
00:11:30,500 --> 00:11:32,041
And here comes the
fearsome Master,

224
00:11:32,125 --> 00:11:35,416
stalking down the walkway
in his devil panda style!

225
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:38,333
[KAGE] He knows how to make
an entrance, that's for sure!

226
00:11:38,416 --> 00:11:40,583
Wow! As quickly as this
fight was organized,

227
00:11:40,666 --> 00:11:43,041
it's shocking he
has so many fans!

228
00:11:43,125 --> 00:11:44,958
One might even say
it defies credibility,

229
00:11:45,041 --> 00:11:47,458
but I'm just here for the ride!

230
00:11:47,541 --> 00:11:50,000
[KAGE] I'm not surprised.
He's clearly got the right mix

231
00:11:50,083 --> 00:11:52,041
of scowling and
flamboyant weirdness

232
00:11:52,125 --> 00:11:53,875
to be a charismatic heel!

233
00:11:53,958 --> 00:11:56,208
[MASUTO] Let's see if
he can work the crowd.

234
00:12:01,208 --> 00:12:04,083
[FANS cheering]

235
00:12:04,166 --> 00:12:07,083
[MASUTO] And work it he does!
With his Extreme Akiba Pose!

236
00:12:07,166 --> 00:12:09,625
The fans are warmed
up and ready to go!

237
00:12:12,750 --> 00:12:14,083
[MASUTO]
Ooh, and what's this?

238
00:12:14,166 --> 00:12:16,875
Diva Risa is entering
the ring with a mic!

239
00:12:16,958 --> 00:12:20,583
Listen up, all you weak
little boys of Akiba!

240
00:12:21,958 --> 00:12:24,375
I went all the way to China
to find me a real man,

241
00:12:24,458 --> 00:12:26,333
and now he's gonna
help me conquer you!

242
00:12:26,416 --> 00:12:30,166
This is bad, fans! Diva Risa
wants to rule over us all!

243
00:12:30,250 --> 00:12:31,708
[RISA]
And who's gonna stop me?

244
00:12:31,791 --> 00:12:35,125
You so-called vigilantes who
pretend to defend this town?

245
00:12:35,208 --> 00:12:37,000
Well I'm sure it's fun
to act like sheriffs,

246
00:12:37,083 --> 00:12:39,041
but I don't remember
anyone giving you badges,

247
00:12:39,125 --> 00:12:40,875
so excuse me if I don't shiver!

248
00:12:40,958 --> 00:12:42,083
[KUROBUGS cheer]

249
00:12:42,166 --> 00:12:43,250
[MASUTO]
She's right,

250
00:12:43,333 --> 00:12:44,708
the vigilantes have
no legal authority!

251
00:12:44,791 --> 00:12:46,791
Just the unwritten
code of the street!

252
00:12:46,875 --> 00:12:50,791
[KAGE] Maybe so, but at least
their intentions are good!

253
00:12:50,875 --> 00:12:52,166
[VIGILANTES]
Risa sucks!

254
00:12:52,250 --> 00:12:54,250
[RISA] Scream all you want,
babies, I won't stop!

255
00:12:54,333 --> 00:12:56,875
If I have to knock you out
one by one to get my way,

256
00:12:56,958 --> 00:12:58,166
that's fine with me!

257
00:12:58,250 --> 00:13:00,333
--♪
--[FANS cheering]

258
00:13:00,416 --> 00:13:03,083
[MASUTO]
Wait! That entrance music!

259
00:13:03,166 --> 00:13:04,708
Could it be?

260
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:09,791
[ARISA giggles]
Moi!

261
00:13:12,833 --> 00:13:16,000
[ANNOUNCER] And his opponent.
From Helsinki, Finland,

262
00:13:16,083 --> 00:13:22,833
weighing in at a fierce
112 pounds, Arisa Ahokainen!

263
00:13:22,916 --> 00:13:25,166
[FANS cheer]

264
00:13:25,250 --> 00:13:27,833
[MASUTO] You heard that right!
It's Arisa Ahokainen,

265
00:13:27,916 --> 00:13:29,833
from the rising stars
of the vigilante world,

266
00:13:29,916 --> 00:13:32,666
Electric Mayonnaise and Friends!
Tonight she'll defend the

267
00:13:32,750 --> 00:13:34,708
name of unlicensed
crime-fighters everywhere,

268
00:13:34,791 --> 00:13:37,375
and try to put Diva
Risa's plans on ice!

269
00:13:37,458 --> 00:13:38,666
[KAGE]
These are both accomplished

270
00:13:38,750 --> 00:13:41,458
kung-fu martial artists!
So get ready, fans,

271
00:13:41,541 --> 00:13:45,000
this should be an incredible
fight worthy of the hype!

272
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:49,958
Moi, Master, you have to
wake up, it's not too late!

273
00:13:50,041 --> 00:13:52,458
You can't let this promoter-
slash-appliance-reseller

274
00:13:52,541 --> 00:13:53,583
ruin you!

275
00:13:53,666 --> 00:13:54,833
[MASUTO]
Ooh!

276
00:13:54,916 --> 00:13:56,750
It sounds like these two
have some history, Kage!

277
00:13:56,833 --> 00:13:58,208
[KAGE]
Indeed they do.

278
00:13:58,291 --> 00:14:00,750
Arisa was actually
Master's apprentice.

279
00:14:00,833 --> 00:14:02,583
Least that's what it
says in the press kit.

280
00:14:02,666 --> 00:14:03,708
[MASUTO]
I know it hasn't started yet,

281
00:14:03,791 --> 00:14:04,833
but I'm calling it anyway.

282
00:14:04,916 --> 00:14:07,041
This is the fight
of the century!

283
00:14:08,291 --> 00:14:10,500
[MASUTO] And we're off!
Akiba's fate is on the line,

284
00:14:10,583 --> 00:14:12,708
and the rules of this match
are extremely hardcore!

285
00:14:12,791 --> 00:14:14,500
This won't be easy for Arisa.

286
00:14:14,583 --> 00:14:15,916
[KAGE] That's right!
Because other than

287
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:18,416
three-counts-and-your-out,
there are no rules!

288
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:20,708
Not only is Master
a kung-fu champion,

289
00:14:20,791 --> 00:14:23,083
but who knows what
Risa has up her gloves!

290
00:14:23,166 --> 00:14:25,375
[MASUTO] Yes, Arisa will have to
keep an eye on her opponent

291
00:14:25,458 --> 00:14:27,541
and her back!

292
00:14:27,625 --> 00:14:30,791
In terms of raw power,
it seems Arisa has the edge.

293
00:14:32,041 --> 00:14:34,458
[MASUTO] But he uses it against
her and throws her to the ropes!

294
00:14:34,541 --> 00:14:36,291
Astounding technique!

295
00:14:36,375 --> 00:14:37,625
[grunts]

296
00:14:37,708 --> 00:14:39,208
[MASUTO] And there it is!
Our first chair attack!

297
00:14:39,291 --> 00:14:41,541
[KAGE] That hurts even more
when you don't see it coming!

298
00:14:41,625 --> 00:14:42,708
Hey! No fair!

299
00:14:42,791 --> 00:14:45,416
Didn't you hear?
This is a no-rules fight!

300
00:14:45,500 --> 00:14:46,708
[REF grunts]

301
00:14:46,791 --> 00:14:48,833
[MASUTO] The ref is down!
Earlier than usual!

302
00:14:48,916 --> 00:14:51,500
[RISA]
Now! Use the chair!

303
00:14:54,041 --> 00:14:55,958
[ARISA gasps]
Yes, I knew it!

304
00:14:56,041 --> 00:14:57,541
[RISA]
What? Disobeying?

305
00:14:57,625 --> 00:15:00,250
Don't you care what
happens to them?

306
00:15:00,333 --> 00:15:02,875
[MASUTO] Oh no! Looks like
Master's family is being

307
00:15:02,958 --> 00:15:05,333
held hostage in some sort
of lettuce labor camp!

308
00:15:05,416 --> 00:15:06,916
[KAGE] Yes, looks like
a mountain village

309
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:09,708
lettuce labor camp.
Those are the worst.

310
00:15:09,791 --> 00:15:11,333
Do it!

311
00:15:11,416 --> 00:15:13,000
[MASTER grunts, shouts]

312
00:15:13,083 --> 00:15:14,750
[ARISA]
No, Master. Fight it!

313
00:15:14,833 --> 00:15:17,541
[ARISA shouts]

314
00:15:17,625 --> 00:15:18,458
[BROADCASTERS gasp]

315
00:15:18,541 --> 00:15:19,291
Dios Mio!

316
00:15:19,375 --> 00:15:20,291
Arisa no!

317
00:15:20,375 --> 00:15:22,333
[MASUTO]
This is looking dangerous!

318
00:15:25,916 --> 00:15:28,208
[MASUTO] Is he really
going to jump from there?

319
00:15:28,291 --> 00:15:29,291
[grunts]

320
00:15:29,375 --> 00:15:31,958
[MASUTO] That's Master's
Tombstone Bomb!

321
00:15:32,041 --> 00:15:35,291
[MASUTO] Oh no! Our
Spanish-language broadcasters!

322
00:15:35,375 --> 00:15:37,583
[FANS cheering]

323
00:15:37,666 --> 00:15:41,458
[KAGE] That was awesome!
I mean, I hope they're okay.

324
00:15:41,541 --> 00:15:42,666
[MASUTO]
What do we have here?

325
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:45,833
Master is pulling out...
a kendo stick!

326
00:15:45,916 --> 00:15:48,708
[ARISA grunts]

327
00:15:53,291 --> 00:15:53,958
[MASTER shouts]

328
00:15:54,041 --> 00:15:54,875
[ARISA gasps]

329
00:15:54,958 --> 00:15:56,333
[MASUTO]
His weapon attack fails!

330
00:15:56,416 --> 00:15:58,708
[grunting]

331
00:15:58,791 --> 00:16:01,833
[MASUTO] Now Arisa unloads
with rapid-fire chops!

332
00:16:01,916 --> 00:16:03,541
She's unstoppable!

333
00:16:03,625 --> 00:16:06,875
[ARISA yells]

334
00:16:09,416 --> 00:16:11,041
[MASUTO] What is that
on the mega-screen?

335
00:16:11,125 --> 00:16:14,458
[KAGE] I think those are
the locker rooms. But why?

336
00:16:16,041 --> 00:16:18,416
I'm sorry. I let my
guard down, Arisa.

337
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:19,250
It's my fault.

338
00:16:19,333 --> 00:16:21,000
Please rescue us, big bro!

339
00:16:21,083 --> 00:16:23,041
[MASUTO] They're from Electric
Mayonnaise and Friends!

340
00:16:23,125 --> 00:16:27,208
This is a full-blown disaster!
They've been taken hostage, too!

341
00:16:27,291 --> 00:16:28,750
[ARISA, TAMOTSU]
Oh, no!

342
00:16:28,833 --> 00:16:30,333
[FANS cheering]

343
00:16:30,416 --> 00:16:32,333
[KAGE]
Very dirty move!

344
00:16:32,416 --> 00:16:34,916
Time to end this nonsense
and bow down to me!

345
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:37,083
Lest you don't care what
happens to your friends!

346
00:16:37,166 --> 00:16:39,708
Aw damn it, I was wondering
where they were!

347
00:16:39,791 --> 00:16:40,208
[growls]

348
00:16:40,291 --> 00:16:42,166
Ma! Niwaka!

349
00:16:42,250 --> 00:16:43,958
[grunts]

350
00:16:44,041 --> 00:16:45,875
[MASUTO] Master launches
his counter-attack,

351
00:16:45,958 --> 00:16:48,458
with Arisa afraid to fight back!

352
00:16:48,541 --> 00:16:49,916
No, Master! Stop!

353
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:52,583
[RISA] Ha! Your only
choice is surrender!

354
00:16:52,666 --> 00:16:54,291
[MASUTO] Even for a
no-holds-barred fight,

355
00:16:54,375 --> 00:16:55,333
this is brutal!

356
00:16:55,416 --> 00:16:56,750
[ARISA grunts]

357
00:16:56,833 --> 00:16:58,916
[MASUTO] There it is, folks!
The infamous move!

358
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:00,583
Master's Shaming Spread!

359
00:17:00,666 --> 00:17:03,500
[KAGE] Punishing both physically
and psychologically!

360
00:17:03,583 --> 00:17:05,333
Great camera work, though.

361
00:17:05,416 --> 00:17:08,666
I can't fight or my
teammates will suffer.

362
00:17:08,750 --> 00:17:09,666
What do I do?

363
00:17:09,750 --> 00:17:11,833
I can't just stand
here and watch!

364
00:17:11,916 --> 00:17:12,375
[TAMOTSU grunts]

365
00:17:12,458 --> 00:17:13,791
[ARISA grunts]

366
00:17:13,875 --> 00:17:16,833
[MASUTO] Master releases her!
What is he up to now?

367
00:17:16,916 --> 00:17:19,833
I think I see a table!

368
00:17:19,916 --> 00:17:22,541
Oh! Make that
tables with an "s"!

369
00:17:22,625 --> 00:17:24,208
[KAGE]
No doubt about what this means.

370
00:17:24,291 --> 00:17:27,041
He's setting up his
trademark high-altitude move,

371
00:17:27,125 --> 00:17:28,708
the Last Emperor Press!

372
00:17:28,791 --> 00:17:30,916
[MASUTO] He's climbing
the extra-tall ladder!

373
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:32,333
[KAGE]
Nice and slow.

374
00:17:32,416 --> 00:17:34,583
[MASUTO] If he pulls this off,
the match will be over!

375
00:17:34,666 --> 00:17:35,541
Right, Kage?

376
00:17:35,625 --> 00:17:36,916
[KAGE]
Oh yeah!

377
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,208
This was his finisher in the
Chinese tournament, too.

378
00:17:39,291 --> 00:17:42,916
--[ARISA grunts]
--[engine revs]

379
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:43,416
What the--?

380
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:44,250
Tamotsu!

381
00:17:44,333 --> 00:17:49,291
[FANS]
TM2, TM2, TM2...!

382
00:17:49,375 --> 00:17:50,666
[KUROBUGS growl]

383
00:17:50,750 --> 00:17:55,291
[KUROBUGS grunt]

384
00:17:55,375 --> 00:17:56,666
You guys okay?

385
00:17:56,750 --> 00:17:57,458
Yeah, now!

386
00:17:57,541 --> 00:17:59,083
I knew you'd come save us!

387
00:17:59,166 --> 00:18:00,750
[KAGE]
His daring rescue worked.

388
00:18:00,833 --> 00:18:03,500
This frees up Arisa for
her own counterattack!

389
00:18:03,583 --> 00:18:06,041
Damn you!

390
00:18:06,125 --> 00:18:07,250
[ARISA grunts]

391
00:18:07,333 --> 00:18:08,833
[ARISA shouts]

392
00:18:08,916 --> 00:18:12,166
[MASUTO] Could it get any more
intense?! A triple-table slam!

393
00:18:12,250 --> 00:18:15,208
And both fighters are down!

394
00:18:15,291 --> 00:18:18,833
Now's your chance, Master!
While she's still reeling!

395
00:18:18,916 --> 00:18:21,416
Use this to finish her
once and for all!

396
00:18:25,458 --> 00:18:28,416
You do want to save
your family, don't you?

397
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:30,375
What, don't you care?

398
00:18:34,541 --> 00:18:39,000
[RISA gasps, grunts]

399
00:18:39,083 --> 00:18:40,791
Hey! What the hell was that?

400
00:18:40,875 --> 00:18:42,625
You're attacking
the wrong woman!

401
00:18:42,708 --> 00:18:44,041
My wushu is sacred.

402
00:18:44,125 --> 00:18:47,083
I did not master these
arts for dastardly deeds.

403
00:18:47,166 --> 00:18:49,166
[MASUTO] A shocking
betrayal by Master!

404
00:18:49,250 --> 00:18:51,500
What could've caused
this sudden turn?

405
00:18:51,583 --> 00:18:52,875
[KAGE]
Maybe head trauma?

406
00:18:52,958 --> 00:18:55,375
He crashed through
those tables pretty hard!

407
00:18:55,458 --> 00:18:57,833
Or maybe it was Risa's
slap that did it.

408
00:18:57,916 --> 00:18:59,875
Wouldn't that be ironic?

409
00:18:59,958 --> 00:19:01,625
[MASTER, RISA grunt]

410
00:19:01,708 --> 00:19:06,541
[MASUTO]
Oh! And Diva Risa is down!

411
00:19:06,625 --> 00:19:08,125
Master.

412
00:19:08,208 --> 00:19:12,041
This fight is not over.
I trust you understand.

413
00:19:12,125 --> 00:19:13,625
[ARISA grunts]

414
00:19:16,708 --> 00:19:21,666
[MASTER, ARISA
grunting, shouting]

415
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:34,583
[MASUTO] Here comes his killer
Clothesline from Mapo Tofu!

416
00:19:34,666 --> 00:19:36,416
Oh! A crushing counter!

417
00:19:36,500 --> 00:19:39,500
She smashes his
groin like a gong!

418
00:19:40,666 --> 00:19:42,583
Now brace yourself, Master!

419
00:19:44,625 --> 00:19:45,916
[MASUTO]
This is it, folks!

420
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:49,541
Arisa's signature
finishing move!

421
00:19:49,625 --> 00:19:50,791
[KAGE] She calls it her

422
00:19:50,875 --> 00:19:54,500
"Lovely Final: The End
of Attack!" Very catchy!

423
00:19:55,750 --> 00:19:57,750
[MASTER groans]

424
00:19:57,833 --> 00:20:02,208
[FANS cheer]

425
00:20:02,291 --> 00:20:03,750
[gasps]

426
00:20:03,833 --> 00:20:07,625
[FANS]
One, two... three!

427
00:20:07,708 --> 00:20:09,250
[bell rings]

428
00:20:09,333 --> 00:20:11,625
[MASUTO] The Master-Apprentice
Fight of the Century is over,

429
00:20:11,708 --> 00:20:13,708
and the apprentice has won!

430
00:20:13,791 --> 00:20:15,750
--[RISA shouts]
--[ARIS grunts]

431
00:20:15,833 --> 00:20:17,666
[MASUTO]
Uh, oh! Bad news for Arisa!

432
00:20:17,750 --> 00:20:19,625
[KAGE] She spent all
her energy on Master.

433
00:20:19,708 --> 00:20:21,500
Is there anything
left in the tank?

434
00:20:21,583 --> 00:20:23,333
Because of you,
my sinister scheme

435
00:20:23,416 --> 00:20:25,666
to buy and resell rice
cookers is ruined!

436
00:20:25,750 --> 00:20:27,375
I can't forgive you for that!

437
00:20:27,458 --> 00:20:28,375
♪

438
00:20:28,458 --> 00:20:29,791
[MASUTO]
What does this music mean?

439
00:20:29,875 --> 00:20:32,333
[KAGE]
Looks like Tamotsu is back!

440
00:20:32,416 --> 00:20:34,875
Akiba belongs
to everybody, lady!

441
00:20:34,958 --> 00:20:36,875
There's no way I'll allow
a monster like you

442
00:20:36,958 --> 00:20:37,833
to ruin our town!

443
00:20:37,916 --> 00:20:39,833
[FANS cheer]

444
00:20:39,916 --> 00:20:43,458
[RISA grunts]

445
00:20:43,541 --> 00:20:47,041
Now get ready for a
face-full of Tamotsu!

446
00:20:52,333 --> 00:20:54,875
Even if you strike me down,
you won't be free!

447
00:20:54,958 --> 00:20:56,916
Another reseller
will take my place!

448
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:58,333
Then I'll crush them too!

449
00:20:58,416 --> 00:21:01,916
Your only choice is surrender!

450
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:06,416
[KAGE] It's the legendary Two
Platoons World of Gonzo!

451
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:15,250
[MASUTO]
They did it!

452
00:21:17,708 --> 00:21:21,291
Sorry, Arisa. I hate that I
caused such chaos in your town.

453
00:21:21,375 --> 00:21:24,625
Don't worry, it's no big deal!
I'm a resilient girl, you know!

454
00:21:24,708 --> 00:21:26,958
[MASTER chuckles]
Yes I do.

455
00:21:27,041 --> 00:21:30,041
I'm just happy it's over now.
And you're safe.

456
00:21:30,125 --> 00:21:32,833
It's looks like your
family's safe, too.

457
00:21:32,916 --> 00:21:34,500
Obviously I need
to get stronger

458
00:21:34,583 --> 00:21:37,041
if I can be manipulated
by somebody like her.

459
00:21:37,125 --> 00:21:39,166
I'm restarting my
training from scratch.

460
00:21:39,250 --> 00:21:42,708
Remember everyone! We vigilantes
will keep you safe in Akiba,

461
00:21:42,791 --> 00:21:44,041
you can take that to the bank!

462
00:21:44,125 --> 00:21:47,000
[FANS cheer]

463
00:21:47,083 --> 00:21:49,125
Yeah! We'll defend the
peace no matter what,

464
00:21:49,208 --> 00:21:51,875
so moi moi for now and
have fun shopping, guys!

465
00:21:51,958 --> 00:21:54,333
We're Electric Mayonnaise,
so help us to help you!

466
00:21:54,416 --> 00:21:56,208
Now let's have one last cheer!

467
00:21:56,291 --> 00:21:59,500
[ALL]
Electric Mayonnaise!

468
00:22:00,708 --> 00:22:05,666
[FANS] Electric Mayonnaise!
Electric Mayonnaise...!

469
00:22:13,208 --> 00:22:18,166
♪


470
00:23:43,750 --> 00:23:44,583
[MATOME]
Stop, Tamotsu!

471
00:23:44,666 --> 00:23:45,791
Your life points
dropped to zero!

472
00:23:45,875 --> 00:23:47,666
If you continue this
card battle, you'll die!

473
00:23:47,750 --> 00:23:49,291
[TAMOTSU] Sorry, Mayo.
It's out of my hands.

474
00:23:49,375 --> 00:23:51,875
[MATOME] No! Next episode:
"Tamotsu Falls!"

475
00:23:51,958 --> 00:23:53,541
[TAMOTSU] No! I'm playing
a title-change card!

476
00:23:53,625 --> 00:23:55,916
Now it's. "Whoa, I Battled
with Game Cards!"

477
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:58,166
[MATOME] From now on,
it's my turn forever!

